parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause fires, which can lead to vehicle damage, injury, or even death.
symptoms: Burning smell
smoke
melted plastic
electrical odors
burning wires
and fires originating from the instrument panel
rear dome light fixture
or HVAC electrical system.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Seat Control Module Failure (Fire Hazard)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power seat control module can cause the heated seats to malfunction, leading to a fire hazard.
symptoms: Heated seats running out of control
burning sensation on the skin
and a fire hazard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear door/liftgate lock actuator can cause the door to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to access the cargo area, and potentially leading to safety issues in emergency situations.
symptoms: Loud noise when locking the rear door
periodic failure of the door to open
and the door becoming stuck in a locked or unlocked position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HVAC system can cause electrical components to overheat, leading to a fire hazard.
symptoms: Burning smell
smoke
and electrical odors coming from the vents
and the resistor and connector overheating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of brake lines can cause a sudden loss of braking power, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake fluid leaks
brake warning lights illuminate
loss of braking power
vehicle continues to roll or move without braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic brake control computer can cause the ABS and traction control systems to malfunction, leading to loss of vehicle control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: ABS and traction control systems malfunction
warning lights illuminate
loss of braking power
vehicle instability.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Lift Gate and Window Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear lift gate and window can cause inconvenience, safety hazards, and difficulties in accessing cargo, especially in emergency situations, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rear lift gate and window do not open
the key fob or interior door locks do not unlock the lift gate
there is no manual or emergency access to the lift gate
the lift gate is stuck in the locked or unlocked position
and the lift gate actuator stops working.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear liftgate/latch can cause the door to become stuck, making it impossible to access the cargo area or exit the vehicle in an emergency, which can lead to safety risks, especially in situations like fires or accidents.
symptoms: The rear liftgate/latch does not lock or unlock
the door does not open
the door does not respond to the remote key
the door does not have a manual unlock mechanism
the door does not have a key lock
the latch appears to be defective.
